Kwagga Smith of South Africa in action during day two of the Emirates Dubai Rugby Sevens &#8211; HSBC Sevens World Series match between South Africa and Uganda Picture: Tom Dulat / Getty Images The Blitzboks rugby team opened their 2016/17 World Sevens Series account at the Dubai Sevens with a comfortable 46-0 win over tournament debutants Uganda on Friday. Neil Powell s team were rampant scoring eight tries with newly crowned World Player of the Year Seabelo Senatla scoring twice and captain Philip Snyman also adding a brace. The Blitzboks moved to the top of Pool B with the victory after Scotland beat the USA 14-5 in their opening match. South Africa s Blitzboks face both the Scots and the USA later in the day. The South African Women s Sevens team were beaten 39-0 by New Zealand in the quarterfinals earlier on Friday. Blitzboks Scorers: South Africa Tries: Werner Kok Philip Snyman (2) Seabelo Senatla (2) Rosko Specman Ruhan Nel Kwagga Smith Conversions: Branco du Preez (2) Justin Geduld Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share